(341, 'Destination Manager | Agadir (Maroc)', 'https://www.rekrute.com', 'Rekrute', '', '17/02/2025', 'Non spécifié', 'Non spécifié', 'Non spécifié', '', 'Non spécifié', '1 poste(s) sur Agadir et région - Maroc', 'Non spécifié', 'Hôtellerie / Restauration (métiers de) - Tourisme (métiers du) - Secteur Hôtellerie / Restauration - Tourisme / Voyage / Loisirs', 'Non spécifié', 'CDD', 'Bac Minimum', 'Non spécifiée', 'De 1 à 3 ans', 'Destination Manager - Agadir Hôtellerie / Restauration (métiers de) - Tourisme (métiers du) - Secteur Hôtellerie / Restauration - Tourisme / Voyage / Loisirs De 1 à 3 ans 1 poste(s) sur Agadir et région - Maroc Bac Minimum Organisation Flexibilité Sensibilité émotionnelle Conventionnel Extraversion CDD Télétravail : Non Poste avec Management Publiée aujourd\'hui sur ReKrute.com - Postulez avant le 17/02/2025 J\'aime Suivre Entreprise : Jet2holidays offer their Award-Winning Real Package Holidays across Agadir & Marrakech, and we are looking for people to join our Award-Winning Red Team! Jet2holidays is the UK\'s largest package holiday provider. We take our customers on their well-earned breaks to more than 75 sun, city and ski destinations across Europe. Join Jet2holidays and you\'ll become part of the Jet2 plc success story. We have a devoted team of more than 17,000 colleagues supporting the ever-growing demand for Jet2.com<http://Jet2.com> and Jet2holidays. Poste : We have a fantastic opportunity to join Jet2holidays as a Destination Manager. As one of our valued Destination Managers, you will play a vital part in managing our operation in Agadir. You will hold the most senior position in destination, coaching, developing and overseeing your direct report Team Leaders who manage their respective teams of Customer Helper -Representatives in the resort and airport operations. You will ensure your full team are delivering outstanding customer service and enhancing our customers holiday experience both in the airport and resorts. You will work as one team with internal & external suppliers and stakeholders to take responsibility for your teams\' performance using Management Information (MI) and our in-house digital systems. What will you do in the role? Reporting into the Regional Manager who is based remotely, you will have overall responsibility for managing the planning, budgeting and delivery of the Jet2holidays service across Agadir, producing strong performance and results ensuring you: Collaborate with our local agents, transfer providers, hoteliers and senior UK stakeholders to achieve set KPIs ensuring company policies, procedures and service level agreements are met. Managing costs and delivering against your budget and customer service metrics. Demonstrating effective leadership and taking responsibility for managing all operational disruption, including in destination crisis situations, flight programme delays and customer escalations Manage the performance of your team by hosting scheduled in-person & virtual team meetings, delivering training to new and existing members of your team & hold individual monthly 1-1 performance and welfare meetings with your Team Leaders. Propose key business decisions in the destination using available MI, analysing trends as well as utilising your local destination knowledge. Monitoring, managing and reporting operational disruption which impacts the customers Jet2holiday experience including building works, local events and industrial action. Leading by example displaying role model behaviours and company values in managing and delivering your operation. Profil recherché : What will I need? The successful candidate will have previous management experience in a similar Holiday or Cruise Operations role. You will possess experience of leading and managing large operational teams, ideally including Team Leader level. With a proven track record of delivering results and managing budgets, you will be able to make considered decisions in tight timeframes. An effective communicator, preferably with (location) language skills, you will have excellent stakeholder management skills and the ability to effectively use and interpret data and MI, as well as being IT literate. As we employ on local employment contracts, you will already hold the full right to work documentation required for Morocco. Due to the level of travel required in the role, you will be required to hold a full and valid driving licence and have your own car. Business Travel expenses are reimbursed. What can we offer you? We offer our valued colleagues a range of benefits including: - Local employment contract Competitive salary, with annual pay review Discretionary management bonus scheme Monthly Car Allowance Coaching, development & career progression across Jet2.com & Jet2holidays 3 x salary life assurance Recommend a Friend bonus scheme Apply today to join the UK’s number One Tour Operator! Once your application has been reviewed, you will be contacted by our Jet2holidays recruitment team to advise you of next steps. We look forward to your application & the start of your career with Jet2holidays! Adresse de notre siège : The Mint Sweet Street, LS11 9AW, Leeds, West Yorkshire, United Kingdom Leeds Traits de personnalité souhaités : Organisation Flexibilité Sensibilité émotionnelle Conventionnel Extraversion 4K Matching global N/A N/A FineTunePro COMPÉTENCES N/A Kapacity Revealer PERSONNALITÉ N/A Feel Good CULTURE Ici, vous pouvez retrouver un taux de recommandation de cette offre pour vous, ainsi que des informations pour mettre en avant votre candidature. Connectez-vous / Inscrivez-vous pour consulter ces informations personnalisées. ReKrute vous offre ce nouveau test de personnalité pour mieux vous connaitre et valoriser vos candidatures. Passez-le dès maintenant, cela ne prend que 5 minutes maximum. Bienvenue ! Se connecter Créer un compte Se connecter avec Google ou Adresse email Mot de passe Mot de passe oublié ? Caps Lock Is On Rester connecté Je me 